blog.description:
No One Ever Made a Difference by Being Like Everybody Else ----------------------------------------------------------------Hey there! My names are Claire and Aquila (I have two names). I'm an agender 18 year old ace/aro furry and I live in the UK. If you need to rant or complain or whatever, just drop me an ask! You don't have to apologise or ask if it's okay because as far as I'm concerned, as soon as you follow me, you're my friend! And I love receiving messages and asks from my friends!
Please no nsfw and I don't respond to chainmail. Please refrain from any mention of drugs, suicide or self harm, unless you need to vent in which case, feel free to direct message me to keep it private. Bear in mind I am not equipped to help you with your problems, but I am here to listen.
Check out my YouTube channel Aquila Calvitium!
Thanks for stopping by and I hope you have a great rest of your day!

summary: With a Kadabra as my only team member I take on Roark. His German name is Veit and he's sending in a Geodude. Dude didn't stay...
body:
With a Kadabra as my only team member I take on Roark. His German name is Veit and he’s sending in a Geodude. Dude didn’t stay on the field for long.

Kadabra is still a fast powerhouse and all of his rock Pokémon were no match for its Confusion.

Because Kadabra is my only Pokémon, that means, it’s getting all the exp. So, naturally, I’m overlevelled right now.

That will fix itself once I get more members of my party.

Speaking of, I went through Eterna Woods with a really nice girl, Cheryl, who healed my Kadabra after every fight. That was so nice of her and her Chansey.

And once we were on the other side of the forest, in Eterna City, I knew what to do next.

Catching Pokémon! Look at these two! Isn’t Bronzor adorable? It’s ability is Levitate, so it’s the perfect ability. It can protect my team against such powerful moves as Earthquake. I called it Ben, after the bell in Big Ben Tower. It’ll be a bell someday after all.

And then, look at this. The return of MC Hammer! My perfect little Meditite! It even has the right ability Pure Power! Which, if I recall correctly, is the only ability it can get prior to Gen 5, but I’m calling it a win anyway!

And with the improvement of Gen 4, it’ll be even more useful than it was back in Hoenn! Because now a move’s category is determined by the move itself rather than the type of the move.

Fire Punch? Physical. Shadow Ball? Special. So much more sense now.

And I found a good use for the Pokétch. It displays my party, so I can keep track of it at any time. Piplup is still on the team, because it not only learns Rock Smash but also Cut, both moves I need to proceed.

summary: This is Chu, the Pikachu! I found him at a thrift store, and despite him being a dime a dozen plush, I brought him home anyway...

He’s a lorge boi, not as lorge as one that I think I may have rehomed, but he’s still pretty big. He’s a good boi, and Chu is a wonderful member of the Pokefamily

Espeon and Dragonair fusion

Psychic/Dragon Type

The Morning Dragon Pokemon
